Introduction:
-------------

	- Python add-ons for
	  - Richard Taylor's (r.taylor@bcs.org.uk) Python-wrapper-classes "pyrapi" around
	    - "librapi2" a part of
	      - David Eriksson's "SynCE"-project (http://synce.sourceforge.net/)

	Rem: Above indentation is intentionally.


Contents:
---------


CE_DirView.py
	Based on the QT-Example "dirview".
	I wrote this, because I wanted a GUI but unfortunately I've only
	KDE-2 installed and don't want to upgrade to KDE-3 right now.
	Perhaps this is an alternative for other people also, who don't
	want or can use SynCE-KDE.

	Imports:  "PreferencesDialog.py"


pyrapi (package)
	Client who connects to a real pyrapi-server.
	This means: On the other end "CE_DirViewServer.py" has to run and
	import the real "pyrapi.py". "CE_DirViewServer.py" is packaged
	with pyrapi in the contrib/qt directory.


DebugPrint.py
	Utilities for debug printing.


Depends:
--------

PyQt


License:
--------

In keeping with the license of pyrapi...

MIT License, see the file LICENSE for details.


Instructions:
-------------

	1. Define the server. This has to be done only once!

	   $ python pyrapi/pyrapi.py -h host [-p port]

	   Where host is the name or IP of the computer running "CE_DirViewServer.py".

	2. Start the client. E.g.:

	   $ CE_DirView.py

	   or on MacOS X
	   
	   $ pythonw CE_DirView.py

	Use "pydoc CE_DirView" to get more info.


How it works:
-------------

	This scheme shows how the "fake" pyrapi-module and "CE_DirViewServer.py"
	can be inserted transparent between an pyrapi-addon and the
	"real" pyrapi-module.
	The pyrapi-addon is "CE_DirView.py".


	Example call: CeMoveFile


	1. Computer with SynCE installed. Direct connection.

		CE_DirView.py
			CALL pyrapi.CeMoveFile (...) -> pyrapi 


	#--------------------------------------------------


	2. Computer without SynCE installed. Network connection.

		CE_DirView.py
			CALL pyrapi.CeMoveFile (...) -> 
		
			pyrapi/pyrapi.py				[ FAKE / CLIENT ]
				SUB CeMoveFile (...)
					CALL ProcessStream ("CeMoveFile", ...)
		
			========== NETWORK ==========
		
		CE_DirViewServer.py					[ SERVER ]
			SUB HandleStreamRequest (...)
				if Cmds [0] == "CeMoveFile": ...
					CALL pyrapi.CeMoveFile (...) -> pyrapi


Have fun!

